      <section eId="sec_CHC-526">
        <num>CHC 526</num>
        <heading>526. Â Immunity from civil or criminal liability</heading>
        <subsection eId="CHC-526__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>A board member, staff member, or volunteer of a child advocacy center shall not be liable for civil damages, while acting in the official scope of his or her duties, if the person in good faith makes a recommendation, gives an opinion or releases or uses information for the purpose of protecting a child.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-526__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>The limitation of civil liability in Paragraph A of this Article does not apply if a board member, staff member, or volunteer of a child advocacy center acts with gross negligence or in bad faith.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=113455</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
